In this article, President Biden provides an update on the response to Hurricane Ian in Florida and the approaching storm in South Carolina. He mentions the actions taken to save lives and provide support, including approving emergency declarations for both states and deploying search and rescue teams. The President emphasizes the devastating impact of the storm in Florida and expresses solidarity with the affected communities. He also highlights the efforts to restore power and clear debris, as well as the ongoing recovery efforts in Puerto Rico. In addition to the hurricane update, President Biden addresses remarks made by Russian President Putin, stating that the United States and its allies will not be intimidated and will continue to support Ukraine in defending its territory. The President announces new sanctions against Russia and emphasizes the unity of NATO allies in countering Russian aggression. He also mentions an act of sabotage on a pipeline and the efforts to enhance its protection.